      - `code_suffix` calls `free_suffix`
      - `free_suffix` might call `be_code_freeregs` which decrements `freereg`
      - This could free the register that `key` was stored in!
   
   The fix is to evaluate `c` first, THEN evaluate `k`. This way, when `k` is
   evaluated after `c`, it won't be affected by any register freeing that
   happens during the evaluation of `c`.
   
